TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
Suppose the solutions of a quadratic equation \(p(x) = 0\) are 
\(3\) and \(-5\).  Then that quadratic equation can be written
as
$BCENTER
\(p(x) = x^2 + \)
  \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(x -\)
 \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(=0.\)
$ECENTER
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(2));
ANS(num_cmp(15));


BEGIN_TEXT;
$BR $BBOLD Hint: $EBOLD  Think of \(p(x) \) as \((x-3)(x+5)\).
END_TEXT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD

\[p(x) = (x-3)(x+5)= x^2 +2x-15.\]
EOT





